snippet.textDisplay:
It's not just Ocarina Link that's strong! I'm a little sad that you included Wind Waker Link in the thumbnail, but didn't mention his equally impressive strength at all!


-He can lift or push around stone obstacles of various heights and shapes with no assistance (including large stone puzzle blocks).
-He does a deadlift-toss of gigantic stone heads MULTIPLE TIMES throughout the game with only the addition of the power bracelets. He also moves with them much more easily than Ocarina Link does with the limestone or granite blocks (he's able to lift them, spin in place, walk around, and throw them with very little effort).
-He hauls around a bag with pouches full of other stacks of items, a bag of up to 99 bombs the size of his head, iron boots, his hookshot, a whole ship's sail, and a heavy metal-and-bone hammer as big as his entire body.
-He uses pretty much only metal shields (Hylian and Mirror shield).


He's much smaller than Ocarina Link as well, so I feel that adds to the potential of Wind Waker/"Toon" Link to (at least) be in the running for strongest of all Links.

He's much smaller than Ocarina Link as well, so I feel that adds to the potential of Wind Waker/"Toon" Link to (at least) be in the running for strongest of all Links.
